Seplat Petroleum Development Company Plc has donated three security vehicles to the Nigeria Police, Nigerian Navy and the Nigeria Security and Civil Defense Corps (NSCDC) in Ugborhen Community in Delta State. The vehicles were procured from the community’s Freedom To Operate (FTO) account. Ugborhen is one of SEPLAT’s foremost oil and gas host communities in Ovhor field in OML 38 & 41, a swampy terrain in Okpe Kingdom in the Western Niger Delta. The presentation of the three Toyota Hilux vehicles was done at the Ugborhen Community town hall. The company also provided technical input on the type of vehicle to be procured and provided guidance on how to make the agreement with the security agencies workable. Though procured by the community, Seplat helped in inspecting the vehicles and ensured the vehicles are fit for the intended purpose. Speaking on behalf of Seplat, chief executive officer of the company, Roger Brown, represented by the Base office manager, Western Assets, Mr Emmanuel Otokhine, reiterated the company’s commitment to partnering with host communities in creating shared business values. Mr Brown restated Seplat’s commitment to sustainable development in its host communities, saying the company will continue to promote security in its areas of operation and beyond, whilst urging the citizenry to continuing to remain peaceful at all time. At the event, various speakers commended the community and Seplat for the collaboration geared towards strengthening security in the area. The Police, the military and NSCDC officers expressed joy as they stressed that the support will assist in ensuring effective policing that will engender peace in the community and the Sapele Local Government Area at large. 